      • plot

        public void plot(StressSequence sequence,
                 boolean plotPosInc,
                 boolean plotNegInc,
                 boolean[] plotStep)
        Plots mission profile for the given stress sequence.
        Parameters:
        sequence - Stress sequence.
        plotPosInc - True to plot positive increments.
        plotNegInc - True to plot negative increments.
        plotStep - Step plotting options. Array size must be 8 (for 8 steps). Null can be given for plotting all steps.

      • plottingCompleted

        public void plottingCompleted(org.jfree.data.xy.IntervalXYDataset incrementDataset,
                              org.jfree.data.xy.XYDataset steadyDataset,
                              org.jfree.data.xy.XYDataset incrementPointsDataset,
                              java.util.ArrayList<Segment> segments,
                              double maxDiff,
                              java.lang.String title,
                              java.lang.String subTitle)
        Called when plotting process has ended.
        Parameters:
        incrementDataset - Dataset which contains increment stresses as intervals.
        steadyDataset - Dataset which contains steady stresses.
        incrementPointsDataset - Dataset which contains increment stresses as points.
        segments - List of segments.
        maxDiff - Maximum difference in plot to adjust Y axis.
        title - Chart title.
        subTitle - Chart subtitle.
